The paper deals with the capacity region of a broadcast channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the transmission of messages to subsets of receivers, which is related to multicast communication (cs.NI). The paper discusses the achievable rates for the channel, which is a topic in network information theory (cs.SI). The characterization of the achievable rate region involves constraints on the geometry of the region, which is related to computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of network coding for L=3, which is a topic in distributed systems (cs.DS) and computer communication (cs.CC).
